            <h4>
                Effects of arithmetic operations
            </h4>
                <ul>

                    <li>
                        Adding or subtracting a constant moves the whole
                        distribution. The mean moves, the spread remains
                        unchanged.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Multiplying or dividing by a constant spreads or
                        narrows the distribution. The standard deviation is
                        multiplied (or divided) by that constant.
                    </li>
                </ul>

        </details>

